oakcurric:unit-3171
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Communication and the world around us: Repaso - la vida diaria y en línea"@en ;
  curric:slug "media-and-technology-repaso-la-vida-diaria-y-en-linea" ;
  rdfs:comment """This first revision unit covers all persons of the present and preterite. Pupils
  strengthen direct objects and modal verbs. They contrast the preterite and imperfect, use
  imperfect forms of 'estar' with a present participle to discuss actions in progress, and
  use the preterite for interruptions."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils refresh previously learned grammar and vocabulary in
  the context of everyday living. They reactivate their knowledge of the present and preterite
  including irregular verbs that they have learned throughout the course. Pupils anchor their
  knowledge of direct object pronouns and direct objects in one-verb and two-verb constructions
  in the context of shopping, supported with the use of modal verbs. Pupils form the present
  and imperfect continuous including irregulars, and accurately describe events in the past
  using the preterite and imperfect.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3171-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3171-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3171-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3171-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3171-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3171-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3171-7 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3171-8 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3171-9 ;
  curric:id "3171"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.100203Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-questions .

oakcurric:unit-3518
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Studying and my future: Repaso - el colegio y el trabajo"@en ;
  curric:slug "studying-and-my-future-repaso-el-colegio-y-el-trabajo" ;
  rdfs:comment """This revision unit covers the present tense in-depth. Pupils revisit 'ser' and
  'estar', the present continuous, idiomatic phrases, and use of 'usted'. Pupils also
  strengthen the preterite and imperfect."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils fine-tune uses of the present tense to talk about
  life in school and work. They use the present continuous and idiomatic phrases, form nouns,
  and revisit a variety of vocabulary. They embed formal language with 'usted' and possessive
  adjective 'su' to ask questions formally. Having consolidated 'ser' and 'estar' multiple
  times throughout the course, pupils now confidently differentiate these two verbs. Pupils
  reflect on their past experiences at school using the preterite and imperfect.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3518-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3518-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3518-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3518-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3518-5 ;
  curric:id "3518"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.394233Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-negation ,
    oakcurric:thread-questions ,
    oakcurric:thread-adjectives ,
    oakcurric:thread-extend-written-and-spoken-production .

oakcurric:unit-3162
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "People and lifestyle: cuestiones de identidad"@en ;
  curric:slug "my-personal-world-cuestiones-de-identidad" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit introduces singular and plural forms of 'haber' with an -ar verb stem
  and '-ado', and an -er or -ir verb stem with '-ido'. Pupils learn some irregular past
  participles. The unit introduces 'hay que', 'se puede', 'se necesita', 'se debe', and the
  passive 'se' with the third person."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils learn a new way to talk about the past using singular
  and plural forms of 'haber' with an -ar verb stem and '-ado', and an -er or -ir verb stem
  with '-ido' to form the perfect tense. They learn some irregular past participles, and will
  learn more in a future unit. Pupils revisit the imperfect tense and practise the perfect
  tense whilst learning about the experiences of Spanish-speaking migrants. Pupils learn 'hay
  que' to talk about what people have to do, and are introduced to the passive with 'se'.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3162-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3162-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3162-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3162-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3162-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3162-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3162-7 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3162-8 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3162-9 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3162-10 ;
  curric:id "3162"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.479183Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-past ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-word-order ,
    oakcurric:thread-extend-written-and-spoken-production .

oakcurric:unit-3154
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "People and lifestyle, Popular culture: la vida fuera y dentro del colegio"@en ;
  curric:slug "my-personal-world-la-vida-fuera-y-dentro-del-colegio" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils revisit irregular verb stems 'tuve' and 'hice', and learn new
  irregular stems. Pupils consolidate the second person singular for -er and -ir verbs in
  the preterite and now learn the second person plural. They learn 'sin' with an infinitive
  to mean 'without doing'."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils consolidate a variety of regular and irregular verbs
  in the present and preterite, and expand this with irregular preterite stems 'pude', 'vine',
  'puse', 'quise', 'traje', 'estuve', 'dije'. Pupils build on their knowledge of forms of the
  preterite with the second person plural of -er and -ir verbs. They will learn the second
  person plural of -ar verbs in another unit. Pupils anchor a variety of infinitive structures
  while talking about routines, and add 'sin' with an infinitive to their repertoire. Pupils
  already know how to use 'conmigo', and expand this with 'contigo'.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3154-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3154-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3154-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3154-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3154-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3154-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3154-7 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3154-8 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3154-9 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3154-10 ;
  curric:id "3154"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.481997Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-nouns-and-determiners ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-past ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-extend-written-and-spoken-production .

oakcurric:unit-3155
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "My personal world: la migración y la identidad nacional"@en ;
  curric:slug "my-personal-world-la-migracion-y-la-identidad-nacional" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit introduces plural forms of 'ir' in the preterite. Pupils revisit
  singular forms of 'ir' in the preterite, and all forms of 'ser', contrasting both verbs.
  Pupils learn patterns for nationality adjectives, and revisit rules for forming feminine
  nouns."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils anchor their knowledge of 'ir' and 'ser' in the
  preterite to learn about a family's migration. Pupils expand their knowledge of 'ir' in the
  preterite by adding plural forms, and contrast 'ir' and 'ser' in the preterite, as this is an
  area of linguistic difficulty. Pupils learn adjective patterns for nationality, and refresh
  nominalising masculine adjectives to form languages, in the context of discussing cultural
  background and national identity. They apply knowledge of 'ser' in all persons to talk
  further about identity.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3155-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3155-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3155-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3155-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3155-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3155-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3155-7 ;
  curric:id "3155"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.484514Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-past ,
    oakcurric:thread-listen-and-respond-to-longer-passages ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-word-order .

oakcurric:unit-3158
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "People and lifestyle: en el instituto"@en ;
  curric:slug "studying-and-my-future-en-el-instituto" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit introduces possessive adjectives 'mío/a', 'tuyo/a', 'suyo/a', and
  possessive pronouns 'el mío', 'la mía', 'el tuyo', 'la tuya', 'el suyo', 'la suya'. Pupils
  also learn irregular superlative adjectives 'el mejor' and 'el peor'. Pupils revisit
  possessive and demonstrative adjectives."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils consolidate possessive adjectives 'mi', 'tu', 'su' by
  contrasting them with new possessive adjectives 'mío/a', 'tuyo/a', 'suyo/a'. Pupils further
  their knowledge with possessive pronouns 'el mío', 'la mía', 'el tuyo', 'la tuya', 'el suyo',
  'la suya'. Pupils embed their knowledge of demonstrative adjectives 'este', 'esta', 'ese',
  'esa' in sentences using possessive adjectives and pronouns. Pupils are introduced to the
  superlative with irregular adjectives 'el mejor' and 'el peor'. They will learn how to form
  regular superlatives in another unit.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3158-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3158-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3158-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3158-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3158-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3158-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3158-7 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3158-8 ;
  curric:id "3158"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.513027Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-adjectives ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-extend-written-and-spoken-production .

oakcurric:unit-3157
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "People and lifestyle: Los desafíos del mundo actual"@en ;
  curric:slug "lifestyle-and-wellbeing-los-desafios-del-mundo-actual" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit revisits singular forms of 'ser' in the imperfect, and introduces plural
  forms. Pupils learn how form sentences with neuter 'esto' and 'eso', the comparative
  'tan...como', suffixes '-ito' and '-ita' to form the diminutive, and suffixes '-ísimo' and
  '-ísima' to express 'very'."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit revisits singular forms of 'ser' in the imperfect, and expands
  pupils' knowledge with plural forms. Pupils strengthen their understanding by contrasting the
  imperfect with the present. Pupils anchor third person forms of 'ser' and 'estar' with
  demonstrative adjectives in sentences with new comparative 'tan...como', and with new
  suffixes '-ito', '-ita', -ísimo' and '-ísima' to talk about the natural world. Pupils
  maintain working memory of prenominal adjectives, relative clauses, indefinite adjectives,
  adjective-noun gender and number agreement, and interrogative pronouns.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3157-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3157-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3157-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3157-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3157-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3157-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3157-7 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3157-8 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3157-9 ;
  curric:id "3157"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.556996Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
