oakcurric:unit-3150
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Travel and tourism: nuevas experiencias"@en ;
  curric:slug "travel-and-tourism-nuevas-experiencias" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit revisits singular forms of the preterite, including first person
  spelling changes, and introduces the addition of 'y' in some third person preterite verbs.
  Pupils learn 'alguno' as an indefinite adjective, and the syntax of questions with
  prepositions."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils refresh their knowledge of the preterite and build on
  this with the addition of 'y' in some third person preterite verbs. Pupils ask yes/ no
  questions using raised intonation and further their knowledge of questions by learning syntax
  of questions with prepositions. They reactivate their knowledge of indefinite articles, and
  learn the indefinite adjective 'alguno'. Pupils will add 'ninguno' in a later unit. They
  refresh a range of grammatical concepts from KS3 including plural rules, prenominal
  adjectives, and rules surrounding when to use or omit subject pronouns.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3150-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3150-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3150-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3150-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3150-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3150-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3150-7 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3150-8 ;
  curric:id "3150"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.648700Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight ,
    oakcurric:thread-nouns-and-determiners ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-past .

oakcurric:unit-3163
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Popular culture: estrellas y famosos"@en ;
  curric:slug "media-and-technology-estrellas-y-famosos" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit introduces irregular verb 'dar' in singular and plural forms in the
  preterite. Pupils contrast the preterite forms of 'dar' with their present tense versions.
  They revisit idiomatic uses of 'dar' with nouns of emotions. Pupils form the passive with
  'ser' and a past particple and 'por'."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils broaden their knowledge of the preterite with
  irregular verb 'dar'. They embed 'dar' in the present tense, and contrast it with the
  preterite. Pupils revisit 'dar' with nouns of emotion in the present tense, and build on this
  knowledge by using this structure in the preterite. Pupils already know how to form past
  participles and how to conjugate 'ser'. In this unit, they use 'ser' with a past participle
  and 'por' to form the passive.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3163-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3163-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3163-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3163-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3163-5 ;
  curric:id "3163"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.736155Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-present .

oakcurric:unit-3161
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Travel and tourism: nuevos lugares"@en ;
  curric:slug "travel-and-tourism-nuevos-lugares" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit revisits singular forms of the inflectional future tense, and introduces
  plural forms. It also introduces further irregular stems. Pupils learn pronouns
  'alguno/a/os/as' and 'ninguno/a/os/as', the present tense with 'desde hace', and 'llevar'
  with a time period and present participle."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils build on their knowledge of the inflectional future
  tense with plural forms and further irregular stems. Pupils consolidate singular forms and
  practise plural forms in the context of planning a trip. They embed comparative structures
  whilst comparing their destination with their home country. Pupils consolidate indefinite
  adjective 'algún' and contrast it with pronouns 'alguno/a/os/as' and 'ninguno/a/os/as'.
  Pupils use 'desde hace' and 'llevar' with a time period and present participle to talk about
  how long they have been doing something in the context of cities.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3161-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3161-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3161-3 ,
