    oakcurric:thread-meaning-and-purpose ,
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-past ,
    oakcurric:thread-extend-written-and-spoken-production .

oakcurric:unit-3152
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Travel and tourism: la cultura popular y tradicional"@en ;
  curric:slug "travel-and-tourism-la-cultura-popular-y-tradicional" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit introduces the affirmative imperative of second person singular -ar, -er
  and -ir verbs. Pupils revisit 'ser' and 'estar', the present tense with simple and
  continuous functions, and the present continuous. Pupils learn spelling changes for the
  present participle where stems end in a vowel."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils learn the affirmative imperative of second person
  verbs to give instructions to someone visiting a festival such as La Tomatina. Pupils
  strengthen first person forms of 'estar' with a present participle, and build on this with
  present participles with spelling changes where the stem ends in a vowel, or verbs like
  'pedir'. Pupils embed knowledge of a range of grammatical structures such as possessive
  adjectives, reflexives, plural rules, and position of adverbs of location with 'del' and 'de
  la' in the context of customs and festivals.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3152-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3152-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3152-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3152-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3152-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3152-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3152-7 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3152-8 ;
  curric:id "3152"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.853155Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-present .

oakcurric:unit-3519
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "People and Lifestyle: Repaso - consejos de vida"@en ;
  curric:slug "lifestyle-and-wellbeing-repaso-consejos-de-vida" ;
  rdfs:comment """This revision unit focuses on a variety of moods and tenses. Pupils revisit the
  second person singular and plural imperative including irregulars, the conditional and
  impersonal verbs."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit allows pupils to reactivate a broad range of grammatical
  concepts that they have learned on this course, enabling them to confidently use their
  Spanish in a large variety of tenses, scenarios and contexts. Pupils anchor the imperative in
  the context of household chores and organising, and they use impersonal verbs and the
  conditional to give recommendations for a healthy lifestyle.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3519-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3519-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3519-3 ;
  curric:id "3519"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.039845Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-past ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-future-and-conditional .

oakcurric:unit-3151
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Lifestyle and wellbeing: la vida de todos los días"@en ;
  curric:slug "lifestyle-and-wellbeing-la-vida-de-todos-los-dias" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit revisits direct and indirect object pronouns with object-first word
  order. Pupils learn the word order for direct and indirect pronouns in two-verb
  structures, and indirect object pronouns 'nos' and 'os'. They revisit a variety of
  present-tense and modal verbs."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils already know direct object pronouns 'lo', 'la', 'los', 'las' and
  indirect object pronouns 'me, 'te, 'le', 'les' in one-verb constructions. They also know
  modals 'querer', 'poder', 'deber', and 'tener que', and 'sé'. In this unit, they build on
  this knowledge with word order for direct and indirect pronouns in two-verb structures.
  Pupils expand indirect object pronouns with 'nos' and 'os'. They also revisit -er and -ir
  verbs in the present tense as well as irregular verbs, ensuring accuracy of language.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3151-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3151-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3151-3 ,
