oakcurric:unit-3517
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Studying and my future: mi futuro y mis modelos a seguir"@en ;
  curric:slug "studying-and-my-future-mi-futuro-y-mis-modelos-a-seguir" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils revisit the inflectional future tense, including some
  irregular stems. Pupils revisit 'quisiera' and 'me/te/le gustaría' and learn how to form
  the conditional tense with regular verbs and some irregular verbs."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit initially revisits the inflectional future, including regular
  forms and irregular stems, which pupils embed in the context of aspirations and role models.
  This provides a useful foundation for an introduction to forming verbs in the conditional
  tense, which uses the same stems. Pupils are also already familiar with singular 'gustar' in
  the conditional, which is revisited here. Pupils anchor their new knowledge of the
  conditional to discuss what they would like to do post-16, and to talk about an ideal world.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3517-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3517-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3517-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3517-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3517-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3517-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3517-7 ;
  curric:id "3517"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.277089Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-future-and-conditional ,
    oakcurric:thread-extend-written-and-spoken-production .

oakcurric:unit-3156
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "My neighbourhood: la vida en México"@en ;
  curric:slug "my-neighbourhood-la-vida-en-mexico" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit introduces new structures for forming negative statements, and revisits
  verbal negation with 'no'. Pupils learn second person plural -ar verbs in the preterite,
  and contrast this with the singular. They revisit -ar verbs in the present tense, stem
  change verbs, and possessive adjectives."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils can already negate verbs using 'no'. In this unit, they expand
  their knowledge of negation to use structures with 'nada', 'nunca', 'nadie', 'ninguno', 'ya
  no', and 'no...ni...ni'. Pupils have already learned the second person plural of -er and -ir
  verbs in the preterite, and now they add -ar verbs to their repertoire. They reactivate their
  knowledge of second person singular -ar verbs in the preterite, contrasting them with the
  plural. Pupils refresh working memory of stem change verbs, verbs like 'dirigir', possessive
  adjectives 'tu' and 'vuestro', position of adverbs, and 'conmigo'.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3156-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3156-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3156-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3156-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3156-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3156-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3156-7 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3156-8 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3156-9 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3156-10 ;
  curric:id "3156"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.307275Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 ;
