    oakcurric:thread-listen-and-respond-to-longer-passages ,
    oakcurric:thread-read-and-respond-to-texts .

oakcurric:unit-3165
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "My personal world: relaciones"@en ;
  curric:slug "my-personal-world-relaciones" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit introduces new forms of possessive adjectives as a post-verbal
  complement, and new forms of possessive pronouns with agreement for gender and number for
  singular and plural possessors. Pupils also learn the reflexive use of plural forms of
  pronouns including with a reciprocal function."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit revisits possessive pronouns and possessive adjectives as a
  post-verbal complement with agreement for gender for singular possessors. It builds on this
  prior knowledge by introducing agreement for number and plural possessors, which pupils use
  in the context of discussing what belongs to people on holiday. Pupils learned singular
  reflexive pronouns in a previous unit. Now they learn plural reflexive pronouns 'nos' 'os'
  'se', including how to use these pronouns with a reciprocal function. Pupils revisit a
  variety of grammatical structures to support active recall.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3165-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3165-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3165-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3165-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3165-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3165-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3165-7 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3165-8 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3165-9 ;
  curric:id "3165"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.312287Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-past ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-present .

oakcurric:unit-3153
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Media and technology: actores y películas"@en ;
  curric:slug "media-and-technology-actores-y-peliculas" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit revisits possessive adjectives 'su' and 'sus' meaning 'his', 'her',
  'its', and adds new meaning 'their'. Pupils contrast the third person singular with the
  third person plural of the preterite, and revisit possessive adjectives 'vuestro/a/os/as'."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils already know that 'su' and 'sus' mean his, her or its, and now
  learn that 'su' also means 'their'. Pupils combine this knowledge with the third person
  singular and plural of the preterite, and third person singular and plural pronouns to talk
  about what famous people do by themselves or as a couple. Pupils anchor raised intonation in
  yes/no questions and possessive adjectives 'vuestro/a/os/as' in the context of asking famous
  people about themselves.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3153-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3153-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3153-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3153-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3153-5 ;
  curric:id "3153"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.330218Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight ,
    oakcurric:thread-nouns-and-determiners ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-past .

oakcurric:unit-3520
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Preguntas y respuestas"@en ;
  curric:slug "preguntas-y-respuestas" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit draws together known grammar and vocabulary in practising the skills for
  the different elements of the GCSE examination."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this final unit, pupils apply their knowledge in extended spoken
  production, transcription, listening, reading and responding to longer passages, and extended
  written production. Pupils will also be able to ask and answer questions in role play, photo
  card and conversation practice.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3520-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3520-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3520-3 ,
