  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-listen-and-respond-to-longer-passages ,
    oakcurric:thread-read-and-respond-to-texts ,
    oakcurric:thread-extend-written-and-spoken-production .

oakcurric:unit-3172
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "My neighbourhood: Repaso - perspectivas internacionales"@en ;
  curric:slug "my-neighbourhood-repaso-perspectivas-internacionales" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this revision unit, pupils focus on the present perfect tense. They use all
  persons of 'haber' with stems of -ar, -er, and -ir verbs, and also revise irregular past
  participles."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils draw on their knowledge of the perfect tense to talk
  about how the world has changed, covering matters such as the environment, women's rights,
  black lives matter, migration, and technology. Pupils have learned and revisited the perfect
  tense previously in this course, and now use their in-depth understanding to engage with
  complex topics.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3172-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3172-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3172-3 ;
  curric:id "3172"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.535575Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-past .

oakcurric:unit-3516
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "My neighbourhood: conflictos"@en ;
  curric:slug "my-neighbourhood-conflictos" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit focuses on revisiting the imperfect tense. Pupils revisit imperfect
  forms of 'ir', 'ver', 'ser', -ar, -er, and -ir verbs. They use imperfect forms of 'estar'
  with a present participle for events in progress in the past, and use the preterite for
  interruptions."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils develop a strong grasp of the imperfect tense by
  consolidating what they have learned in previous units. They use this to explore poems
  written by Spanish speakers describing life during conflicts. Pupils refresh -ar, -er, and
  -ir verbs and irregular verbs 'ir', 'ver', 'ser' in the imperfect. They talk about events in
  progress using imperfect forms of 'estar' with a present participle, and combine this with
  relative clauses using 'cuando' and the preterite to describe an interruption.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3516-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3516-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3516-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3516-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3516-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3516-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3516-7 ;
  curric:id "3516"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.560201Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight ,
    oakcurric:thread-read-and-respond-to-texts .

oakcurric:unit-3515
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Popular culture: Fiestas y costumbres"@en ;
  curric:slug "travel-and-tourism-fiestas-y-costumbres" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit introduces idiomatic phrases 'acabar de' with the infinitive, 'seguir'
  with a present participle, and 'continuar' with a present participle. Pupils revisit third
  person singular and plural regular -er and -ir verbs in the preterite, interrogatives and
  question words."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils learned to form the present participle in previous units. Now they
  combine it with 'seguir' and 'continuar' to mean 'to continue to' or 'to still be doing'.
  They also learn the idiomatic phrase 'acabar de' with an infinitive to mean 'to have just'.
  Pupils anchor third person singular and plural regular -er and -ir verbs in the preterite in
  the context of customs and festivals in Spain and Latin America, and secure using rising
  intonation and verb subject word order with question words.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3515-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3515-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3515-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3515-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3515-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3515-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3515-7 ;
  curric:id "3515"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.565226Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight ,
    oakcurric:thread-extend-written-and-spoken-production .

oakcurric:unit-3712
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Travel and tourism: Repaso - de viaje"@en ;
  curric:slug "travel-and-tourism-repaso-de-viaje" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit covers the conditional and inflectional future including irregular
  stems, and pupils revisit impersonal verbs."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit pupils anchor the inflectional future and subjunctive to
  discuss the positives and negatives of travel and tourism.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3712-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3712-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3712-3 ;
  curric:id "3712"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.619143Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-past ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-future-and-conditional .

oakcurric:unit-3168
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Lifestyle and wellbeing: el deporte"@en ;
  curric:slug "lifestyle-and-wellbeing-el-deporte" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils learn to add '-able' to a verb stem to create an adjective
  where the English meaning is '-able'. The addition of 'y' in the third person for some
  present tense verbs is introduced. Pupils learn the second person plural imperative for
  -ar, -er, and -ir verbs."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils already know how to form second person singular verbs in the
  affirmative imperative for -ar, -er and -ir verbs, in addition to some irregulars. Knowledge
  of the imperative is expanded in this unit with the affirmative second person plural. Pupils
  use the imperative in the context of giving commands during sport. In this unit, pupils
  further their ability to manipulate language with the suffix '-able'. Pupils are already
  familiar with irregular verbs in the present tense, and revisit verbs like 'dirigir'. They
  add verbs such as 'incluir' to their repertoire.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3168-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3168-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3168-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3168-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3168-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3168-6 ;
  curric:id "3168"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.001485Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-derivational-word-patterns ,
    oakcurric:thread-listen-and-respond-to-longer-passages ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-present .

oakcurric:unit-3159
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Media and technology: conversaciones"@en ;
  curric:slug "media-and-technology-conversaciones" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit revisits regular comparative structures and irregular comparatives
  'mejor que' and 'peor que', and introduces regular superlative structures. Pupils learn
  'quisiera' with an infinitive and 'me/te/le gustaría' with an infinitive to express 'would
  like to'."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on pupils' knowledge of the superlative, which was
  introduced in the previous unit, with regular superlative structures. Pupils contrast the
  superlative with regular comparative structures and irregular comparatives 'mejor que' and
  'peor que', which they learnt in previous units. Pupils are already familiar with 'querer'
  with an infinitive as a modal verb and now learn its imperfect subjunctive form 'quisiera'
  with an infinitive to express 'would like'. Likewise, pupils learn the conditional form
  'gustaría'.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3159-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3159-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3159-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3159-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3159-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3159-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3159-7 ;
  curric:id "3159"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.945892Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight ,
    oakcurric:thread-adjectives ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-present .

oakcurric:unit-3164
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "People and lifestyle: situaciones diarias"@en ;
  curric:slug "lifestyle-and-wellbeing-situaciones-diarias" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils learn 'usted' to mean formal 'you'. Pupils further their
  knowledge of speaking formally with possessive adjective 'su' meaning 'your'. The unit
  introduces irregular forms of the second person affirmative imperative, and revisits
  regular second person affirmative imperatives."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit introduces new subject pronoun 'usted'. Pupils already know
  possessive adjective 'su' to mean 'his' or 'her', and now learn it also means 'your' in
  formal contexts. They revisit the third person singular in the present tense and learn that
  this form of the verb is used with 'usted'. Pupils strengthen their knowledge of informal
  'tú'. Pupils consolidate regular forms of the second person affirmative imperative, and
  expand their knowledge of the affirmative imperative with irregular forms, which they embed
  in the context of instructions for protecting the environment.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3164-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3164-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3164-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3164-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3164-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3164-6 ;
  curric:id "3164"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.040496Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-present .

oakcurric:unit-3646
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "People and lifestyle: influencias"@en ;
  curric:slug "my-personal-world-influencias" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit furthers pupils' knowledge of the subjunctive. Pupils learn singular
  subjunctive forms of 'ir' and 'venir', and use the subjunctive after verbs of emotion and
  'para que'. Pupils refresh and learn new impersonal verbs, and are introduced to
  adjectival phrases with 'lo' and an adjective."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit introduces the subjunctive. Pupils learn singular subjunctive
  forms of verbs 'tener', 'ser', and 'hacer', and instances when they should use the
  subjunctive. In other units, pupils learned to express the future using the inflectional
  future tense, which is revisited in this unit. Pupils learn to use the subjunctive to express
  the future after conjunction of time 'cuando'. They recap 'quisiera' with an infinitive and
  'me/te/le gustaría' with an infinitive to express 'would like', and contrast this with the
  subjunctive used after verbs of wishing. This unit also revisits the preterite.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3646-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3646-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3646-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3646-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3646-5 ;
  curric:id "3646"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.653118Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-future-and-conditional .

oakcurric:unit-3169
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Travel and tourism: Figuras históricas"@en ;
  curric:slug "travel-and-tourism-figuras-historicas" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils use relative pronouns 'lo que', 'el que', 'el cual' in
  subject relative clauses, and revisit relative clauses using wh- pronouns 'que', 'donde',
  'cuando'. Pupils refresh irregular preterite verb stems."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils learned subject relative clauses in previous units. In this unit,
  they strengthen their use of wh- pronouns as relative pronouns 'que', 'donde', 'cuando', and
  learn new relative pronouns 'lo que', 'el que', 'el cual'. Pupils anchor their knowledge of
  irregular verbs in the preterite in conversations about historical Spanish-speaking figures.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3169-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3169-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3169-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3169-4 ;
  curric:id "3169"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.671149Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight ,
    oakcurric:thread-read-and-respond-to-texts ,
    oakcurric:thread-extend-written-and-spoken-production .

oakcurric:unit-3167
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Popular culture: de compras"@en ;
  curric:slug "lifestyle-and-wellbeing-de-compras" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit introduces demonstrative adjectives 'aquel', 'aquella', 'aquellos',
  'aquellas' and neuter demonstrative 'aquello'. It revisits demonstrative adjectives 'ese',
  'esa', 'esos', 'esas'. Pupils learn plural forms of 'dar', and revisit other irregular
  verbs in the present tense."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In other units, pupils learned neuter 'eso' and demonstrative adjectives
  'ese', 'esa', 'esos', 'esas'. Pupils now build on this knowledge with demonstrative
  adjectives 'aquel', 'aquella', 'aquellos', 'aquellas', and neuter demonstrative 'aquello', to
  indicate objects when shopping. Pupils are already familiar with singular forms of 'dar' in
  the present tense, and now learn plural forms. They recap singular forms of 'hacer', verbs
  like 'poner', and verbs like 'concocer'.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3167-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3167-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3167-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3167-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3167-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3167-6 ;
  curric:id "3167"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.785112Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-nouns-and-determiners ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-present .

oakcurric:unit-3160
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Studying and my future: mi futuro en el trabajo"@en ;
  curric:slug "studying-and-my-future-mi-futuro-en-el-trabajo" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit introduces singular forms of the inflectional future tense for -ar, -er,
  -ir verbs. It also introduces irregular inflectional future stems 'tendr-', 'har-' and
  'podr-'. Pupils revisit 'que' as a relative pronoun in subject relative clauses."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils learn singular forms of the inflectional future tense
  to talk about their future career aspirations. Pupils will learn plural forms in a later
  unit. The unit also introduces irregular inflectional future stems 'tendr-', 'har-' and
  'podr-', with further irregular stems taught in future units.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3160-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3160-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3160-3 ;
  curric:id "3160"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.856175Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-future-and-conditional ,
    oakcurric:thread-extend-written-and-spoken-production .

