  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """It is important to listen out for synonyms and distractors when answering listening
  comprehension questions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.262880Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-29207-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """It is important to have a firm knowledge of Spanish SSCs in order to accurately
  transcribe spoken Spanish."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.265780Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-29207-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """It is important to have a broad vocbabulary to be successful at answering listening
  comprehension questions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.265784Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-29207-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """It is important to listen out for synonyms and distractors when answering listening
  comprehension questions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.265788Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26098-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Víctor Jara was a Chilean songwriter victim of Pinochet's regime due to his
  political activism and support of democracy."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.266342Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26098-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The imperfect tense is used to talk about something that used to happen
  repeatedly."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.266346Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26098-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The verbs 'ir' ('to go, going'), 'ser' ('to be, being') and 'ver' ('to see, seeing')
  are irregular in the imperfect."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.266350Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26098-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "In the imperfect tense, -ar verbs have different endings to -er and -ir verbs."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.266354Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26098-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """In two-verb modal structures, reflexive pronouns can go before the first verb or
  after the infinitive, attached to it."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.266358Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26094-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Use 'acabar de' + infinitive to mean 'to have just done' something."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.266528Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26094-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """'Seguir' + present participle is a two-verb structure meaning ‘to still be doing’
  something."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.266532Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26094-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Present participles in Spanish normally end in -ando or -iendo."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.266538Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26094-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Las Hogueras de San Juan takes place every year on 23rd June in Alicante; it
  celebrates the arrival of summer."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.266542Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26148-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The subjunctive indicates uncertainty, wishing or possibility, or refers to actions
  that have not yet happened."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.266545Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26148-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The conjunction 'para que' translates as 'so that' and is followed by a subjunctive
  verb."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.266549Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26148-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Spanish uses the subjunctive after 'para que' even though English uses the
  indicative after 'so that'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.266553Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-29222-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """It is important to have a firm knowledge of Spanish SSCs in order to accurately
  transcribe spoken Spanish."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.267729Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-29222-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """It is important to have a broad vocabulary to be successful at answering listening
  comprehension questions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.267732Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-29222-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """It is important to listen out for synonyms and distractors when answering listening
  comprehension questions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.267736Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26025-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """To make a noun plural, add -s if it ends in a vowel and -es if it ends in a
  consonant."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.268877Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26025-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """[s] sounds like 'siempre', [z] sounds like 'empezar', [ci] sounds like 'principio'
  and [ce] sounds like 'entonces'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.268881Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26025-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """To say ‘you do something to yourself’, use 'te' before the verb, and 'me' to say 'I
  do something to myself’."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.268885Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26025-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When talking to somebody familiar to you (tú) with the affirmative imperative with
  -er verbs, use the ending -e."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.268889Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26025-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """San Fermín (or San Fermines) is a week-long celebration held annually in Pamplona
  that involves running with bulls."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.268895Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26026-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """To form the present continuous, use 'estar' and a verb in the present participle
  (-ando, -iendo)."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.269773Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26026-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """In Spanish, there are two ways to say ‘to be’. Use ser with permanent traits and
  estar with location, states and moods."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.269777Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26026-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Extended reading texts can be exploited to enrich our thematic vocabulary and use of
  complex structures."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.269780Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26026-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """It is important to communicate accurately but also to include varied and complex
  language."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.269784Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26026-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """It is helpful to reference popular customs and celebrations in different Hispanic
  countries in this topic."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.269787Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26096-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """[ca] is pronounced as in 'casa', [co] is pronounced as in 'comer' and [cu] is
  pronounced as in 'cultura'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.271356Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26096-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When describing a photo, it is important to use full sentences that include
  a verb."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.271359Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26096-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When describing a photo, it is important to convey a range of information about the
  image."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.271363Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26096-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """PALM is a useful acronym for remembering the types of information to include in a
  photo description."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.271369Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26027-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """El día de Muertos is a Mexican celebration whereby people remember and pay homage to
  loved ones who have passed."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.271647Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26027-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """[ll] and [y] are pronounced the same. [ll] sounds like 'llevar' and [y] sounds like
  'ayuda'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.271651Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26027-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The singular present tense forms of 'estar' are 'estoy', 'estás, 'está'."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.271655Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26027-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """'Estar' + present participle of -ar and -er/-ir verbs (-ando, -iendo) is used to
  talk about ongoing events."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.271660Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26027-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Verbs whose stems end in a vowel ('leer', 'construir') have an i->y spelling change
  for the present participle ending."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.271664Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26038-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Preterite endings for -er/-ir verbs are -í, -iste, -ió (singular persons) and -ieron
  (third person plural)."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.273073Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26038-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A detailed description often has a wide range of features."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.273076Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26038-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """We can also use longer texts to enrich vocabulary and style and ensure we include
  varied and interesting language."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.273080Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-29219-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """It is important to have a firm knowledge of Spanish SSCs in order to accurately
  transcribe spoken Spanish."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.273095Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-29219-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """It is important to have a broad vocabulary to be successful at answering listening
  comprehension questions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.273099Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-29219-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """It is important to listen out for synonyms and distractors when answering listening
  comprehension questions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.273102Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26128-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "It is importantly to see words in context to effectively strengthen vocabulary."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.276087Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26128-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The simple present describes habitual actions in the present, e.g. 'I play
  football'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.276091Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26128-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Conversation answers can be developed using adverbs of time and 3rd person
  language."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.276095Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-29212-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """We can boost our word knowledge by making connections between words such as word
  families, synonyms, opposites, etc."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.290355Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-29212-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """To mean 'you' in an informal context, use 'tú'. In a formal context, use
  'usted'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.290359Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-29212-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """It is common to address unfamiliar people as 'usted', for example in commercial
  settings like a shop or restaurant."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.290363Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-29212-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The plural form of 'usted' is 'ustedes'."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.290369Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-29212-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """'Usted' and 'ustedes' respectively take the 3rd person singular and plural forms of
  the verb."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.290373Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26057-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'Ese' means 'that' before a singular or uncountable masculine noun."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.310485Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26057-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'Esa' means 'that' before a singular or uncountable feminine noun."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.310489Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26057-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """'Esos' and 'esas' mean 'those' before plural masculine and plural feminine
  nouns."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.310494Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26057-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Most Spanish adjectives agree in gender and number with the noun."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.310497Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26057-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'Tan ... como' means 'as ...  as' in comparisons."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.310504Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26046-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Masculine nouns ending in -or gain an -a when referring to a woman or girl."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.313250Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26046-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Some nouns relating to jobs have specific feminine forms e.g. el jefe > la jefa."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.313256Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26046-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Adjectives of nationality can be used as nouns to refer to people from a particular
  country."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.313260Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26046-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Cultural icons are people or artefacts identified by members of a culture as
  representative of that culture."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.313264Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26046-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Cultural stereotypes are oversimplified ideas, beliefs or images ascribed to all
  members of a particular culture."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.313268Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26063-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Modal verbs express necessity or possibility, and can be used to communicate future
  hopes and desires."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.313272Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26063-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "To say what you would like to do, use a modal verb followed by an infinitive."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.313276Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26063-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Common modal verbs in Spanish include 'quisiera', 'me gustaría', 'te gustaría' and
  'le gustaría'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.313281Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26084-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The verb 'dar' means 'to give'. 'Doy' means 'I give', 'das' means 'you give' and
  'da' means 'she, he, it' gives."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.314295Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26084-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """In the preterite tense, 'di' means 'I gave', 'diste' means 'you gave' and 'dio'
  means 'she, he, it gave'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.314299Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26084-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "There is no word in Spanish for 'do' or 'did' in questions."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.314303Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26084-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Questions also begin with an upside down question mark."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.314307Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28480-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The definite article is used with body parts rather than ‘my’ ‘yours’, ‘his’/’her’,
  etc."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.315511Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28480-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘Doler’ (to hurt, to be painful) is very commonly used with an indirect object
  pronoun."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.315515Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28480-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """In sentences with ‘doler’, the subject is the body part(s) so you need to use the
  correct verb ending for -er verbs."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.315520Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28480-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """In a role play, you are expected to say a few words or a short phrase in response to
  each prompt/bullet."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.315525Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26085-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """'Damos' means 'we give', 'dais' means 'you all give', and 'dan' means 'they
  give'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.316405Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26085-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """'Dimos' means 'we gave', 'disteis' means 'you all gave' and 'dieron' means 'they
  gave'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.316409Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26085-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The words 'pena', 'alegría', 'vergüenza', 'risa', 'miedo' and 'sueno' are
  all nouns."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.316413Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26085-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'Dar' often appears before a noun of feeling or emotion."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.316417Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26085-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """'Dar' + noun of feeling or emotion normally translates as 'to be' + adjective in
  English."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.316422Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26169-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """It is important to have a firm knowledge of Spanish SSCs in order to accurately
  transcribe spoken Spanish."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.319355Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26169-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """It is important to have a broad vocabulary to be successful at answering listening
  comprehension questions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.319359Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-26169-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """It is important to listen out for synonyms and distractors when answering listening
  comprehension questions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.319363Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28482-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Use the affirmative imperative to tell somebody to do something or to give
  instructions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.320856Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28482-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Regular -ar and -er/-ir imperative verbs end in -a or -e respectively."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.320860Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28482-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """'Hacer', 'decir', 'poner', 'salir', 'ser', 'ir', 'tener' and 'venir' are irregular
  in the affirmative imperative."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.320864Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28482-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The PALM acronym is a useful tool to include a range of information when describing
  photos."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.320871Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28482-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When describing photos in Spanish, it is important to plan extended sentences to
  talk for a prolonged period of time."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.320875Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

